---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service | 5 Cypress Automation"
  description="Terms for using the 5 Cypress Automation website and engaging our business automation services."
>
  <section class="section legal-hero">
    <div class="container legal-wrap">
      <p class="lead-in">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: May 7, 2026</p>

      <article class="legal-card">
        <h2>Services</h2>
        <p>5 Cypress Automation provides business automation consulting, workflow design, implementation, documentation, and support. Project scope, deliverables, pricing, and timelines are defined in a separate proposal or agreement.</p>

        <h2>Client Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>Clients are responsible for providing accurate requirements, timely feedback, access to required tools, and approval before automations are used in live business workflows.</p>

        <h2>Testing and Launch</h2>
        <p>We test automations before launch, but clients should review outputs and confirm workflows before relying on them for production business decisions, payments, invoices, or customer communications.</p>

        <h2>Third-Party Tools</h2>
        <p>Many automations depend on third-party platforms. We are not responsible for outages, API changes, data issues, or limitations caused by those external services.</p>

        <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
        <p>We treat client information, workflows, credentials, and business data as confidential. Credentials should be shared through secure approved methods, not pasted into email or chat.</p>

        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the fullest extent allowed by law, liability is limited to fees paid to 5 Cypress Automation for the applicable project or service period. We are not responsible for indirect damages or lost profits.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about these terms? Email <a href="mailto:nick@5cypress.com">nick@5cypress.com</a>.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-hero { padding-top: var(--space-32); }
  .legal-wrap { max-width: 880px; }
  .legal-updated {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-widest);
  }
  .legal-card {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-10);
  }
  .legal-card h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .legal-card h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .legal-card p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }
  .legal-card a {
    color: var(--brand-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
</style>
